{
  "texts": [
    "By leveraging its capabilities, educators and students can anticipate more efficient, accessible, and innovative approaches to learning and practice [38].",
    "Medical students often struggle with transforming theoretical knowledge into practical skills [39], given the complex interplay between anatomy, patient care, and clinical decision-making.",
    "One major challenge is the overwhelming amount of information medical students must process, organize, and integrate across multiple domains [40,41].",
    "Orthopedics, with its intricate focus on musculoskeletal anatomy, biomechanics, and surgical procedures, demands a good understanding that goes beyond memorization.",
    "Additionally, traditional education models, which rely heavily on rote memorization and oneway instruction, often fail to foster the interactive and exploratory learning required in modern medical practice."
  ]
}